description: Redesign of the Northern Triangle Development as approved under ref P01/1500 on 30 May 2002 to provide 249 one, two and three bed intermediate housing units, a Learning Centre, and a shop/ticket office and storage space.
decision_conditions:
No work shall be begun on the construction of any residential units until full details of a scheme for sound insulation have been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The details shall demonstrate how the residential units will achieve the indoor ambient noise levels specified in condition NT9, and will take into account reasonable ventilation requirements and the location of the particular building relative to potential noise sources including non-residential uses and traffic noises.   

	In order to protect residential amenity.

Informatives
The following guidelines are recommended in terms of provision of ventilation. 
Dwellings falling within Noise Exposure Category B: Acoustic secondary glazed window capable of providing a staggered opening with indirect air route; or acoustically treated acoustic passive vents; or acoustically treated variable speed mechanical air supply unit with at least two specified settings. Dwellings falling within NECC or NECD: Acoustically treated acoustic passive vents; or acoustically treated variable speed mechanical air supply unit with at least two specified settings; or any other acoustically treated system of ventilation such as whole house ventilation approved by the Building Control Inspector.
